The paper deals with process mining techniques applied to data from smart homes for elderly, which involves the use of sensors and the interpretation of sensor data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories. Additionally, the goal of the paper is to extract insights from event logs and identify meaningful event labels, which is a common task in the Data Management (cs.DB) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the application area of smart homes for elderly suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
